title: Senior Islamic State leader killed during US helicopter raid in Syria
description: A senior leader of Islamic State (IS) has been killed during a helicopter raid in northern Syria.

title: Ukraine will need fighter jets to see off Russian threat, Poland's president says
description: The president of Poland has told Sky News that Ukraine will need fighter jets to see off the threat from Russia.

title: Bodies of 18 migrants found in abandoned lorry on highway in Bulgaria
description: Police in Bulgaria have discovered an abandoned truck containing the bodies of 18 migrants who appear to have suffocated.

title: One of China's most high-profile billionaire bankers reported missing
description: One of China's most high-profile billionaire bankers has gone missing after his company said it had lost touch with him.

description: Treading carefully but quickly around her family home, Simge Ozdel is packing up her life.

description: A woman has described how she fought off a suspected kidnapper in a Florida gym.

title: Reporter who helped reveal Navalny assassination plot 'banned' from BAFTAs

title: Humans may need more sleep during the winter, study suggests
description: Humans may need more sleep during the winter, according to a study that will be some comfort to those who struggle to get out of bed during the colder months.

title: Japan space agency abandons rocket launch moments before lift-off
description: Japan's space agency aborted the launch of its first new rocket in more than 20 years after parts of the system failed.

title: Patient develops 'uncontrollable Irish accent' after cancer diagnosis
description: A man in the US who was diagnosed with prostate cancer is said to have developed an "uncontrollable Irish accent".

title: They fled war in Syria for the safety of Turkey - now the earthquake is forcing them back
description: At the Bab-al-Hawa crossing on the Turkey-Syria border, there's a huddled mass of the desperate and displaced.

title: Russia set for joint naval drills 'with hypersonic missile' as major security summit begins
description: Russia is due to take part in a joint naval exercise with China and South Africa that could see the test launch of a hypersonic cruise missile - as Western leaders assemble for a major security conference.
